Database migrations (Alembic)
=============================

Schema changes are versioned here. The database URL is read from the
DATABASE_URL environment variable (.env), not hard-coded in alembic.ini.

Common commands (run from kkb-backend/, with the venv active):

  # Apply all pending migrations (use on a fresh database)
  alembic upgrade head

  # Create a new migration after changing models.py
  alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe the change"

  # See the current revision / history
  alembic current
  alembic history

  # Roll back the most recent migration
  alembic downgrade -1

Adopting Alembic on the EXISTING production database
----------------------------------------------------
The live database already has its tables (they were created by
Base.metadata.create_all). To start tracking it with Alembic WITHOUT
recreating anything, stamp it as already up to date — run this ONCE:

  alembic stamp head

After that, future schema changes flow through:
  1. edit models.py
  2. alembic revision --autogenerate -m "..."
  3. alembic upgrade head

Note: main.py still calls create_all on startup so a brand-new dev
database works out of the box. That only adds missing tables; it never
alters existing ones -- column/constraint changes must go through a
migration.
